"type": "note",
"subtopic": "15. Procedure of Artificial Pollination",
"content": "Flowers with desired features are selected\n\n• Anthers from the mature flower of a plant are carefully removed (emasculation) to prevent self-pollination.\n• After pollination, fruits containing desired seeds are produced.",
