"content": "An ecosystem consists of two main components:\n\n• Abiotic factor is associated with Characteristics.\n• There is a close interaction between the living (called biotic) and non-living (called abiotic) components of the environment.\n• Understanding ecosystems: definition, interaction between biotic and abiotic factors.\n• Forest ecosystem: with its flora and fauna.\n• Interaction between Biotic and Abiotic Factors.",
"explanation": "Definitions:\n• Abiotic factor — associated with Characteristics\n• There — a close interaction between the living (called biotic) and non-living (called abiotic) components of the environment\n• Consumers — further classified as primary or first order consumers, secondary or second order consumers and tertiary or third order consumers\n\nAlso know:\n• Air consists of a mixture of following gases.\n• Allow other living organisms to exist.\n• There are many kinds of ecosystems.\n• A forest ecosystem, like any other ecosystem, consists of biotic and abiotic components.",
