"topicId": "bio-ch4",
"type": "note",
"subtopic": "6. Autotrophs or producers",
"content": "These organisms synthesise their own food by photosynthesis\n\n• Sunlight is associated with Required for manufacturing food by green plants during photosynthesis.\n• Ecosystems depend on sun's energy which is captured by the green plants to produce food.\n• A food relationship exists between plants and animals.\n• Some other examples of food chains are.\n• Plants require carbon dioxide to make food.\n• Green plants need light to make food and to grow.",
"explanation": "Definitions:\n• Sunlight — associated with Required for manufacturing food by green plants during photosynthesis\n• Ecosystems depend on sun's energy which — captured by the green plants to produce food",
