"topicId": "bio-ch4",
"type": "note",
"subtopic": "10. Investigation 3.2",
"content": "Prepare simple food chains on land and in water from the following living organisms :\n\n• Each arrow in a food chain represents “is eaten by”.\n• (d) Algae $ \\rightarrow $ Insects $ \\rightarrow $ Small fish $ \\rightarrow $ Large fish.\n• Food web : In nature, a number of food chains are interconnected.\n• Algae, grass, small fish, crabs, small birds, snakes, lizards, mango tree, grasshoppers, hawk, large fish, mouse, goat and lion.\n• Producers → Herbivores → Small carnivores → Large carnivores.",
"explanation": "Definitions:\n• Water — associated with Helps the plants to carry out photosynthesis; constitutes a major part in a living organism&#x27;s body\n• A food chain — a diagram or a chain showing what organisms eat, or a chain showing the process of “eating and being eaten”\n• Food web : In nature, a number of food chains — interconnected\n\nAlso know:\n• Rather, a number of food chains are interconnected.\n• Apart from the requirement of water for all living organisms, water is required for.\n• Smaller carnivores like birds, lizards and snakes feed on the herbivores.",
