"subtopic": "3. Thyroid Gland",
"content": "The thyroid gland is a bilobed, butterfly-shaped gland. It is located on either side of the wind pipe just in front of the voice box in the neck region. It performs the following main functions:\n\n• Its oversecretion results in increased heart beat, weight loss, increased metabolic rate, etc.\n• Its undersecretion makes the person sluggish, weak and inactive.\n• Thyroxine hormone is synthesized by iodine.\n• An insufficient iodine in diet could lead to the enlargement of thyroid gland which appear as a swelling in the neck.\n• Such glands are called mixed glands.\n• Insulin lowers the blood sugar level in the body.",
"explanation": "Definitions:\n• Hormones — chemical substances secreted by endocrine glands\n• Thyroxine hormone — synthesized by iodine\n• Such glands — called mixed glands\n• Glucose — derived from the food we eat\n\nAlso know:\n• Of glucose to glycogen which gets stored in liver and muscles.\n• Glucagon raises the blood sugar level in the body.\n• Together these hormones maintain the normal blood sugar level in the body.",
"source": "icse",
