"type": "note",
"subtopic": "6. Composition of lymph",
"content": "Lymph does not contain red blood cells, and hence, it is pale and clear\n\n• Yellow in colour is associated with Red in colour due to the presence of RBCs.\n• Yellow in colour — Antigen on RBCs: Red in colour due to the presence of RBCs.\n• Contains WBCs especially lymphocytes which help to develop immunity is associated with Contains RBCs, WBCs and platelets.\n• Contains WBCs especially lymphocytes which help to develop immunity — Antigen on RBCs: Contains RBCs, WBCs and platelets.\n• There are two transport systems in the human body — the circulatory system and the lymphatic system.\n• Lymph vessels have valves to prevent the back flow of tissue fluid.",
"explanation": "Definitions:\n• Yellow in colour — associated with Red in colour due to the presence of RBCs\n• There — two transport systems in the human body — the circulatory system and the lymphatic system\n• Blood — a fluid connective tissue that flows in a closed system of blood vessels\n• Oxygen — absorbed into the blood for circulation\n\nAlso know:\n• Lymph does not contain red blood cells, and hence, it is pale and clear.\n• Large number of leucocytes (mostly lymphocytes) are present in it.\n• About 94% water is present in lymph.\n• Tonsils at the sides of the neck are lymph nodes.",
