"topicId": "bio-ch8",
"type": "note",
"subtopic": "3. Vectors And Vector-Borne Diseases",
"content": "Vectors are organisms, typically insects or other small animals, that carry\n\n• Vector relates to Pathogen, Disease, and Symptoms.\n• Anopheles mosquito (Female) relates to Plasmodium (Protozoan), Malaria, and Periodic fever with chills, red blood cell count drops.\n• Aedes mosquito relates to Yellow fever virus, Yellow fever, and Fever, jaundice, vomiting.\n• Aedes mosquito — Fever, Chill, cold, sneezingCoughingHeadache and weakness: Yellow fever virus.\n• Housefly relates to Entamoeba histolytica (Protozoan), Amoebic dysentery, and Abdominal pain, severe diarrhoea, blood and mucus in faeces.\n• Housefly — Fever, Chill, cold, sneezingCoughingHeadache and weakness: Entamoeba histolytica (Protozoan).",
"explanation": "Definitions:\n• Disease — an abnormal condition of a part, organ, or system of the body which affects the normal functioning of the body\n• Vectors — organisms, typically insects or other small animals, that carry\n• Vector-borne diseases — illnesses caused by the transmission of pathogens through vectors\n• Malaria — transmitted by mosquitoes infected with the Plasmodium parasite\n• Pathogens — defined as Disease-causing biological agents (viruses, bacteria, fungi, protozoa, worms, etc.)\n\nAlso know:\n• Tse-tse fly relates to Trypanosoma (Protozoan), Sleeping sickness, and Fever, rash, fatigue; affects lymph and nervous systems, mental deterioration, increased sleep.\n• Tse-tse fly — Fever, Chill, cold, sneezingCoughingHeadache and weakness: Trypanosoma (Protozoan).\n• Saliva of infected animals (e.g., dogs) relates to Rhabdovirus, Rabies, and Attacks the nervous system, leads to mental confusion, hydrophobia (fear of water), paralysis, and death.\n• Saliva of infected animals (e.g., dogs) — Fever, Chill, cold, sneezingCoughingHeadache and weakness: Rhabdovirus.",
