"explanation": "Definitions:\n• Health — defined as a state of complete physical, mental and social well-being and not merely an absence of diseases\n• Disease — an abnormal condition of a part, organ, or system of the body which affects the normal functioning of the body\n• Personal hygiene — the practice of caring for your body to maintain cleanliness\n• A vaccine — a suspension of disease-producing microorganisms $ \\underline{\\text{microorganisms}} $ which is modified by killing or weakening (attenuated) the microorganisms so that the suspension will not cause disease\n• Antibodies — substances (proteins) which attack the foreign bodies and protect the host from diseases\n\nAlso know:\n• Rather, it stimulates the formation of antibodies upon inoculation.\n• Antibodies are substances (proteins) which attack the foreign bodies and protect the host from diseases.\n• Clothes, especially undergarments, should be changed daily and wearing of very tight clothes must be avoided.\n• One should not defecate in the open.",
