"topicId": "bio-ch8",
"type": "note",
"subtopic": "7. Types of vaccines",
"content": "Vaccines are of different types based on the substances contained in them. The four major type of vaccines are given in table below\n\n• Killed germs is associated with TAB vaccine, Salk&#x27;s vaccine, Rabies vaccine.\n• Killed germs — Examples: TAB vaccine, Salk&#x27;s vaccine, Rabies vaccine.\n• Living, weakened (attenuated) germs is associated with MMR vaccine, BCG vaccine.\n• Living, weakened (attenuated) germs — Examples: MMR vaccine, BCG vaccine.\n• Toxins or poison secreted by patho-gens (Toxoids) is associated with Tetanus toxins, Diptheria toxins.\n• Toxins or poison secreted by patho-gens (Toxoids) — Examples: Tetanus toxins, Diptheria toxins.",
"explanation": "Definitions:\n• Killed germs — associated with TAB vaccine, Salk&#x27;s vaccine, Rabies vaccine\n• Living, weakened (attenuated) germs — associated with MMR vaccine, BCG vaccine\n• Toxins or poison secreted by patho-gens (Toxoids) — associated with Tetanus toxins, Diptheria toxins\n• 2. It — the process of administering a vaccine. is associated with It is the process of making a person immune to a particular disease\n• Disease — an abnormal condition of a part, organ, or system of the body which affects the normal functioning of the body\n\nAlso know:\n• 2. It is the process of administering a vaccine. is associated with It is the process of making a person immune to a particular disease.\n• 2. It is the process of administering a vaccine. — Examples: It is the process of making a person immune to a particular disease.\n• Vaccination is a method of making the body immune to a particular disease.\n• Immunisation is the process by which a person is made immune or resistant to an infectious disease, typically by the administration of a vaccine.",
