"content": "Fungi, along with bacteria bring about the decay of dead plants and animals, both on land and in water. Without microbes, the earth would soon be covered with the dead organisms. There would have been a shortage of…\n\n• Animals obtain nitrogen from food but plants obtain nitrogen from the atmosphere with the help of some nitrogen fixing bacteria.\n• Some bacteria and blue-green algae are the only organisms that can take nitrogen from the air.\n• Other nitrogen fixing bacteria are Nitrobacter and Nitrosomonas.\n• There would have been a shortage of carbon and nitrogen compounds which are essential for the living organisms.",
"explanation": "Also know:\n• Microbes, thus, help in cleaning the environment and recycling of nutrients.\n• Fungi help to increase soil fertility and help in the recycling of nutrients and making the soil fertile.",
