"subtopic": "10. Cash Crops And Food Crops",
"content": "Based on the purpose for which they are grown, crops are classified\n\n• Cereals is associated with Wheat, rice, maize, barley.\n• Plantation crops is associated with Coffee, tea, rubber, coconut.\n• Vegetables is associated with Potato, tomato, brinjal, cabbage, onion, spinach, lady&#x27;s finger, radish, beetroot, turnip, beans.\n• Fruits is associated with Apple, banana, orange, grapes, guava, mango, papaya, pineapple.\n• Flowers is associated with Rose, jasmine, gladiolus, marigold, larkspur, balsam.\n• Ornamental plants is associated with Cactus, crotons, bamboo, china palm, ferns, etc.",
"explanation": "Definitions:\n• Cereals — associated with Wheat, rice, maize, barley\n• Plantation crops — associated with Coffee, tea, rubber, coconut\n• Vegetables — associated with Potato, tomato, brinjal, cabbage, onion, spinach, lady&#x27;s finger, radish, beetroot, turnip, beans\n• Fruits — associated with Apple, banana, orange, grapes, guava, mango, papaya, pineapple\n• Flowers — associated with Rose, jasmine, gladiolus, marigold, larkspur, balsam\n\nAlso know:\n• Ornamental trees is associated with Thuja, christmas tree, Bottlebrush tree, royal palm, Ashoka tree, fishtail palm, etc.\n• Based on the purpose for which they are grown, crops are classified.\n• Cash crops : Crops produced for sale to earn money, rather than for use by the grower.\n• Cash crops is defined as Crops produced for sale to earn money, rather than for use by the grower. In India, a number of cash crops are grown. Examples : Cotton, sugarcane, rubber.",
